      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i see what u mean about human capital, but aren't there basically more direct studies showing that these benefits create a disincentive for people to actually go out and work? like, if the support is too high, why bother with a full-time job? it seems like a pretty clear causal link for a lot of economists.",
